<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="263" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9432: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-17T15:00:00-04:00">August 17, 1937—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>150. Your 272, August 16, 6 p.m. I heartily approve your action and
                            excellent note. If not already done, please inform your British and, in
                            your discretion, French colleague.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>